<p>DirectFlight.net respects intellectual property rights and expects users to do the same. This page describes our copyright policy and the process for reporting alleged infringement under the DMCA and Canadian Copyright Act.</p>
<h2>1. Our Copyright</h2>
<p>All original content on DirectFlight.net — including editorial text, route data, blog articles, design elements, and page layouts — is our intellectual property, protected by Canadian and international copyright law. You may not reproduce, scrape, or create derivative works without our written permission, except as permitted under fair dealing (Canada) or fair use (US).</p>
<h2>2. Third-Party Trademarks</h2>
<p>Airline names, airport names, and booking platform names (Skyscanner, Expedia, Kayak, Google Flights) are trademarks of their respective owners. Their mention on this Site is for informational and affiliate referral purposes only. DirectFlight.net is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or endorsed by any airline or booking platform unless explicitly stated.</p>
<h2>3. Filing a DMCA Notice</h2>
<p>If you believe content on this Site infringes your copyright, send a written notice to <a href="mailto:dmca@directflight.net">dmca@directflight.net</a> including:</p>
<ol>
<li>Identification of the copyrighted work you claim has been infringed</li>
<li>The URL(s) where the allegedly infringing material appears on our Site</li>
<li>Your contact information (name, address, phone, email)</li>
<li>A good faith statement that the use is not authorised by the copyright owner</li>
<li>A statement under penalty of perjury that the information is accurate and you are authorised to act</li>
<li>Your physical or electronic signature</li>
</ol>
<p>We will acknowledge notices within 10 business days and act promptly on valid claims.</p>
<h2>4. Counter-Notification</h2>
<p>If you believe material was removed in error, you may submit a counter-notification to <a href="mailto:dmca@directflight.net">dmca@directflight.net</a> including your signature, identification of the removed material, a statement under penalty of perjury that removal was a mistake, and your consent to jurisdiction of the relevant court.</p>
<h2>5. Permitted Uses</h2>
<p>You may quote up to 100 words from our articles for commentary, review, or news reporting, with a credit link to the original URL. You may share links to our pages. All other reproduction requires our written permission.</p>
<h2>6. Contact</h2>
<p>DMCA: <a href="mailto:dmca@directflight.net">dmca@directflight.net</a> · General: <a href="mailto:hello@directflight.net">hello@directflight.net</a></p>
